t works.  As well as I know, it is based largely on the order of engagement, when someone dies they are taken off the list and the highest person on the hate list (but not on the rampage list) is added.  People often claim to be on the rampage list, then die, get ressed, and are still on it - this is a coincidence with other people dieing and low-hp agro bumping you to the top of the hate list when the new person is chosen for the rampage list, I think.  The rampage list may not be updated automatically either, perhaps only when a rampage goes off (which would also explain zoning out and coming back still on rampage list).  There are exceptions to all of this, of course, which is why there is no definite answer that I have ever seen. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5794">Bippity</a> Hierophant / <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27969">Gobbo</a> 59 Warrior<br><br>Quellious</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uqutsemnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qutsemnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Dar Knight</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/26/02 1:45:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=649.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would you talk to me bout rampage?</span><hr size=1> edit: this was posted while bipp was posting. didnt see her comments.<br><br>i dunno but your question made me think of some better google searches i pulled this out of steel warriors faq<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>What are rampage and flurry?<br>Rampage is an extra attack from a mob that strikes those highest on the hate list. Sometimes rampage seems to attack many people at once, but this isn't always the case. S