ge list.  forever a roguely drain on healing mana.  evade didnt seem to be working against rampage and if it is a second list evade wouldnt be expect to work. so it all fits.<br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uqutsemnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qutsemnie</A> at: 5/26/02 2:02:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/upalaziousfrydaddy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palazious Frydaddy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/26/02 3:09:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=649.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would you talk to me bout rampage?</span><hr size=1> Rampage: On this particular mob I believe it's everything on it's agro list ( extended ) in front of the mob.  I'm usually fairly good at judging my agro and during this particular mob I was busy doing other, more important things like cybering so wasn't nuking very hard &lt;Read: wasn't near top of agro list or even close&gt;.  Alas, the Rampage ate my friggen epic-rune the bastard!  Obviously not a auto-riposte as my melee skillz have been unused since level 30 except to /smack 60 sk's.<br><br>Solution: All but MA staring at the mobs arse.  Not possible on this particular mob due to cornering it.  Just had to eat it, but was weak so /shrug.  I think it was Rumblecrush that ate a raid I was at once, real fast.  Anyone in front of a mob like this just is dead pretty much.<br><br>Flurry:  Kickass round of attacks on whoever has agro?<br><br>Enrage: Auto-riposte? melee turn off Auto-attack i believe. Also affects only those in front of the mob? So, once again MA in front...others on the mobs a$$.<br><br>This right?<br><br>Pal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgco